South Africa’s tax commissioner said on Thursday year-to-date revenue collection was already down R13 billion ($711 million), and was likely get “significantly worse” once coronavirus tax relief measures kick in. “We do anticipate a significant decline in tax revenues purely driven by the state of the economy, as well as the tax relief measures that government has announced,” said South African Revenue Service (Sars) head Edward Kieswetter during a virtual parliamentary briefing.